# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  DESCRIPTION
#
#  A single-file, zero-dependency logging framework that brings the ergonomics
#  of modern structured loggers (zerolog, zap) to Zsh scripts.
#
#  Features:
#    • Four log levels          — ERROR / WARN / INFO / DEBUG
#    • Dual output              — stderr + file simultaneously
#    • Two output formats       — human-readable text and machine-readable JSON
#    • Structured key-value     — attach typed fields to any message
#    • Context loggers          — reusable loggers with pre-attached fields
#    • File rotation            — size-based, multi-process safe (lock file)
#    • Buffered I/O             — batch writes for high-throughput scripts
#    • Async logging            — background worker via FIFO (experimental)
#    • Performance mode         — hot-swap to a fast-path engine (~3–4× faster)
#    • Rate limiting            — cap noisy messages per time window
#    • Log-once                 — emit a message exactly once per key
#    • Benchmarking             — wrap commands or blocks, auto-format duration
#    • Printf-style API         — z::log::infof / warnf / errorf / debugf
#    • Control-flow helpers     — with_level, silent, always, once, rate_limit
#    • Color output             — auto-detected: none / basic / 256 / truecolor
#    • NO_COLOR support         — respects the standard environment variable
#    • Re-entrant safe          — all globals guarded; safe to source many times
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  QUICK START
#
#    source /path/to/zlog
#
#    z::log::info  "Server started"  port 8080 env production
#    z::log::warn  "High memory"     used_mb 1820 limit_mb 2048
#    z::log::error "Connection lost" host db.internal retries 3
#
#  Write to a file as well:
#    z::log::setup "/var/log/app.log" info text
#
#  JSON output:
#    z::log::set_format json
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  PUBLIC API  (prefix: z::log::)
#
#  Core          error / warn / info / debug / log
#  Printf        errorf / warnf / infof / debugf
#  Control-flow  with_level / silent / always / once / rate_limit
#  Context       with_context / remove_context / clear_contexts
#  Benchmark     benchmark / benchmark_start / benchmark_end / benchmark_block
#  Config        setup / set_level / set_file_level / set_format / set_file
#                set_rotation / set_timestamp_format / show_config / reset
#  Buffering     enable_buffering / disable_buffering / flush
#  Async         enable_async / disable_async
#  Performance   enable_performance_mode / disable_performance_mode
#  Diagnostics   get_stats / reset_stats / show_config
#  Cleanup       cleanup / remove_log_file
#
